Pre-Game Insights: The top of Group J is set to have a head to head clash of the leaders as Kenya takes on Cameroon.
The two-legged match is set for Friday, October 11, 2024, at Japoma Stadium in Douala, Cameroon.
There will then be a return leg, behind closed doors at the Mandela National Stadium in Kampala, Uganda on Monday, October 14, 2024.
The Indomitable Lions are approaching the two fixtures as 5-time AFCON champions, 2nd in the all-time list.
Kenya's Harambee Stars ended a 15-year wait to participate in AFCON in 2019, marking their sixth continental tournament appearance.
Kenya has never progressed to the knockout stage of the competition in all their appearances.
Kenya has never beaten Cameroon in 8 different encounters, drawing 4 times and losing the rest while scoring 7 goals. Cameroon has found the net 14 times against Kenya.
Harambee Stars coach was bullish after the last round of fixtures saying 'I am not afraid of Cameroon'.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This will be another international break where Kenyans will not have a chance to watch their national team live due to lack of facilities.
